This Modern/Epoque flat is a few minutes away from Regent's street and Oxford street, the Christmas shopping ground zero streets of London. A home away from home. Perfect spacious apartment to be in Christmas time.

The space
THE FLAT IS LOCATED WITHIN 15 MINUTES WALK OF THE THEATRE DISTRICT. 2 TUBE STATION SERVING 5 LINES.

2 BEDROOMS 2 BATHS Maisonette (two-story apartment) made up of the ground and lower ground floors of Georgian townhouse in central London.

Recently renovated to high standard with very modern bathrooms and kitchen.

The flat's front door opens directly off of the street, it does not share a communal entrance.
Ground floor, which comprises entrance hall, living room, dining room, and kitchen, retains many period features such as original wood panelling, shutters, fireplaces and plaster cornices.
Fully equipped kitchen, feel free to prepare any gourmet me
neighborhood_overview: Neatly tucked away between the wealth of Marylebone, the edgy energy of Soho and the grandeur of Bloomsbury, Fitzrovia is peaceful and attractive, home to small media organisations, small pubs and small restaurants and a smattering of decent hotels. Wide streets lined with tall buildings in Victorian brick mingle with cosy side alleys, with a variety of architectural styles from the eighteenth century to the present day, all of it dominated by the BT Tower, one of London’s tallest and most iconic buildings. Tottenham Court Road is the major shopping street, and the best place in London to look for home furnishings and electronic goods. The area around Oxford Street mixes good high street shops with pubs and bars catching the overflow from Soho’s nightlife.
host_about:
Adventurous,
I am always on the go, I love to travel and have stayed in more than 100 airbnbs around the world. I take great attention to positive criticism and I have learnt a lot through my travels. I try my best to recreate the best environment for my guests.  
I love cinema, theatre and good food! 
London is a great city to live and to explore and my flat is in a great area to explore all London has to offer.

name: Rental unit in Westminster · ★4.89 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
description:
An exciting opportunity to stay in a unique part of London, which is Covent Garden. Enjoy the diversity with its quirky market stalls, pubs, street entertainment and so much more. Enjoy a meal in one of the numerous local restaurants, or book a night at the opera or theatre.

The space
The flat forms part of a listed Edwardian mansion block. It holds a number of original features, is fully furnished and commands an excellent location, being only 2 minutes walk from the Covent Garden tube station and piazza.

Situated in a safe area and normally one of the quieter streets, St Martin's Courtyard is also close by, with it's showcase of fashionable shops and restaurants. A nice touch, are the original street gas lamps that are illuminated in the evening.

The accommodation comprises a cozy and comfortable double sized room with share of the generously proportioned kitchen/diner, bathroom and all available facilities.

The room is carpet
neighborhood_overview: Covent Garden is a happy place to be with a positive and upbeat vibe. Cosmopolitan, with a mixture of people including local residents, local office workers and business people, tourists and the many visitors to the pubs, restaurants and theatres etc.  Home to the Royal Opera House and English National Opera, you will have easy access to all that is available to you and literally on your own doorstep too. Covent Garden is also an ideal springboard location to all the sites and other parts of London and beyond. Truly something to suit everyone and suitable for all age groups, young and and the more mature alike.
host_about:
Originally from South Wales, I have now lived in London for most of my adult life.
 
Worldly in outlook and with a good sense of humour.  Sensible, kind and optimistic with a quietly calm yet confident disposition who enjoys meeting new people. Motto of my first school was "Manners Maketh Man" and I still follow this in my everyday life.

I do not smoke and enjoy the occasional visit to the pub. I also enjoy good food and eat sensibly, at least some of the time anyway!
 
I love living in London with all it has to offer, but equally like to travel from time to time, including the adventure of the odd city break.
 
I enjoy many sports, particularly rugby and boxing, and other interests include listening to many kinds of music, particularly classical and opera.

name: Home in London · ★4.33 · 2 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath
description:
We have an open-plan mid-century home on the edge of Victoria Park, Hackney. It has a 30ft high slanted wooden roof, and sliding patio doors opening onto a self-contained garden. An open staircase leads up to an open kitchen/dining and 2 bedrooms. We are currently renovating so the toilet room is a work in progress as shown in the photos. It is a brand-new toilet. We currently have 2 desks downstairs as we have been working from home.

The space
The mid-century style is unusual in London, yet it gives a sense of space and sanctuary in a very busy city. The wood features are exquisite and the huge glass doors frame a private garden with huge lime trees beyond the garden fence.

Guest access
The whole house and garden. Parking available outside the house.
neighborhood_overview: Victoria Park village is a leafy community near Victoria Park. We have the market every Saturday at London Fields, a 5-minute walk, and every Sunday there is a market in Victoria Park, just 2-minutes walk from our house. In Victoria Park village there is organic meats, a devoted fishmonger, dry cleaning, bakery goods, and a Post Office.
host_about: I am a filmmaker at my small film company Alchemy Films. Making documentaries I travel quite a bit and understand the need for a sanctuary when you are away from home.

name: Rental unit in London · ★4.78 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
description:
Come & stay in this gorgeous high ceiling garden flat in a Victorian era house in Kensal Green, close to Portobello Rd/market, West London. 2 double bedrooms, with separate reception/living room & kitchen. One bedroom faces the pretty rear garden. As it's in a quiet residential area and these old buildings have limited sound insulation, airbnb guests will therefore need to minimise sound production after 9pm in the flat/garden, thus the flat is unsuitable for young or others who like to party.

The space
The flat (apartment) has whitewashed wooden floors and gets lots of sunlight throughout the day. It's peaceful and beautifully quiet. There is a UK/US standard double bed in the master bedroom and a sofa bed (UK/US standard double) in the room at the rear with access to the garden. There is also a sofa in the living room that a small person could sleep on, and a single airbed stored in a cupboard, that can also be removed and used for another person.
neighborhood_overview:
The flat is situated in a peaceful residential street in Kensal Green. Yet there is a decent non-rowdy (ie respectable) pub approx 20 metres from the apartment (that's just 22 yards!) which serves traditional English food, a convenience store 10 metres further (open from 8am till 11pm) selling pretty well every thing including some fruit & vegetables, and beside that a few other shops including an upmarket cafe ('Graceland') with quality healthy meals, and an excellent Italian deli ('L'Angelo'), both of which have both indoor and outdoor seating.
Further shops (including a fish & chips shop & a simple cafe with middle eastern food) are located about 250 metres away to the south - nearly half way to the nearby underground (tube) station (Kensal Green).
Also accessible by foot are the shopping areas of Kensal Rise (600 metres - under 10 mins walk ) and of Salusbury Road (20 minutes walk).
Portobello Road market in Notting Hill is a 5 minute drive away (40 minute walk).
host_about: I love to travel, immerse myself in other's cultures, traditions, street food and entertainment.

description:
Welcome to my lovely home only 3 mins from Pimlico tube @ 10 mins walk from Victoria Station (both in Zone 1) & on the top floor of a modern block.

The flat is stylish and open plan; has very large roof terrace off the living room. You can even see Big Ben, the Houses of Parliament & the London Eye from the main bedroom balcony!

There's a friendly concierge, who's available to help 7am-7pm. Don't miss the built-in coffee grinder and machine.

The space
This is a fantastic penthouse in the heart of Pimlico. Minutes away from transport and lovingly furnished to a very high standard, this is a great space for travellers who want an amazing London experience.

The building is very safe and there's a friendly concierge, who's available to help 7am-7pm, 7 days a week.

The home is very central just minutes away from some of the historical landmarks of London such as Tate Britain, Buckingham Palace, Westminster Cathedral, Westmin
neighborhood_overview: Pimlico doesn’t shout about or show off its many attributes. You might not realise, for example, that it’s ten minutes’ walk to Sloane Square, a stone’s throw from Tate Britain and that Buckingham Palace is within easy reach. It’s also just a brisk half an hour walk to Trafalgar Square and, cutting through St James’s Park, the route is a scenic one too. Plenty of people, however, are in on the ‘secret’ making it a predominantly quiet, residential area with an interesting architectural mix. Victoria, with its coach and railway stations, means the area is a hub for travellers too – the Gatwick Express and Orient Express deliver visitors by the train load to the capital.
host_about:
Management consultant, don't hold that against me:), lived in London for 18 years and in my Pimlico home for 5 years.  Am a passionate pilot, diver and French wine collector - sadly none of these 3 hobbies mix well together!
I believe in living out your dreams so have taken off to work in South Africa for a while.  Hugely proud of my home, have been so happy there and I know you will too.  All the art I have collected in the flat is from friends of mine; love supporting them and only wish I was half as creative.

The second bedroom is very small, but has a double bed - just!

The place is available because we're moving onto a narrowboat for a few months, but it's a small boat so we'll be leaving most of our stuff!

Ideally we'd love to find a guest who might want to take the flat longer term.

Any questions feel free to ask :)

The space
The flats are part of a rather charming Victorian tenement block on a cobbled street - it's a real piece of history and there aren't many places like this left in London.

It is very small, but we think it has real charm. It was our actual home until we moved onto the boat in August 2020 so it has a real homey feel, which people seem to like :)

Guest access
You'll have the whole space to yourselves and it's very private, and surprisingly quiet - being around a traf
neighborhood_overview:
Stoke Newington is a really great neighbourhood to visit. The main street (Church Street) is a two minute walk from our flat, and has a load of unique shops, bars and restaurants. It's one of London's real hidden gems.

There's a gorgeous park at the other end of Church Street, which is great for families - there's an ice cream outlet, a paddling pool, and even some animals like deer and goats.

Dalston (a ten minute walk down the road) is where all the cool kids hang out! It's quite alternative, and there's always lots of interesting things going on, from indie nights, to jazz collectives.

Hackney is the best borough in London if you like an artsy / alternative vibe - there are loads of great markets, shops and bars. Do ask if you want any specific recommendations.

description:
Located in the heart of Mayfair, opposite a Green Park and within easy reach of the underground stations. The Athenaeum Hotel & Residences is one of London’s few award winning family-run 5-star hotels. Its proud heritage and independent spirit is embedded in this luxury hotel’s very fabric: from original Art Deco roots, bespoke British craftsmanship, to the fabulous Living Wall.
NB> On arrival you will be asked for a form of Identification and a credit card to cover any extras.

The space
A small piece of calm and tranquillity in the heart of London. Book Direct for best rates. One of London's most unique hotels. Explore our stylish rooms, suites & residences now. Best Rates Direct. Overlooking Royal Green Park. Family & Pet Friendly. Exclusive Direct Perks.
neighborhood_overview: The Athenaeum hotel is in the heart of Mayfair
host_about:
Independent, award-winning and one of a kind, The Athenaeum retains its crown as London’s foremost family-run five-star hotel. The Athenaeum captures a quintessential spirit of the city. 
Located in the heart of Mayfair opposite the Royal Green Park there is a choice of 134 luxurious rooms, many with views over Green Park; 10 elegant suites with generous open plan layouts and 18 stunning private residences with separate living spaces and dining areas. Situated between Oxford Street, Regent Street, Piccadilly and Park Lane, our central location makes it easy to discover London’s greatest attractions, best shopping areas and theatres of the West End. 
116 at The Athenaeum is a contemporary, British restaurant headed up by Executive Chef, Ian Howard. Relaxed yet chic interiors paired with inimitable service create a warm atmosphere to dine in. The inspiring, seasonal menus champion local producers and use only the very best ingredients.
An intimate setting with floor-to-ceiling windows that showcase our magnificent ‘Living Wall’, The Bar at The Athenaeum is a destination in its own right. Small nooks, plush sofas and leather chairs provide a luxurious environment, while backlit display cabinets show off our prized whisky collection alongside our favourite collectibles from around the world.

Enhanced cleaning protocols and guest well-being measures have been implemented due to Covid-19.

You're just a 20 minute ride from Big Ben, Canary Wharf and main London attractions. Explore the vibrant neighbourhood and easily enjoy the rest of London too. I hope you enjoy your stay!

The space

Located at the heart of the East End, you’re a short walk to the City and the nightlife of Shoreditch. neighborhood_overview:
You will be located in the true East End neighbourhood of Stepney, which first grew up around the church of St Dunstan's - founded 923. With a varied immigrant history including French Hugenots (17thC), Irish (18thC), Ashkenazi Jews (late 19thC), today the population is 47% Bengali, with the best curry houses in London (Needoo Grill is my favourite!).
You can enjoy a walk along the banks of the Thames, with beautiful dockland wharf conversions, an area with a long and proud merchant tradition. To get a sense of the real East End history, head to Wilton’s Music Hall and marvel at one of the only fully working Victorian music hall and vaudeville venues in the UK. For the young/at heart, Stepney City Farm is a wonderful morning out where you can 'talk to the animals' and enjoy an outdoor cafe with London city views.
In the evening, stroll to The Old Ship pub on York Square - said to be the model for the setting for "Eastenders" TV show. It's a proper old fashioned boozer with d
host_about:
My Dad is English and Mum Australian, I was born in Canberra then lived in Sydney for 13 years before moving to London in 2005. 

Am obsessed with music, film, food, books, the arts and theatre.  Which is why I love living in London so much - it's got it all!  I'd be delighted to give you recommendations for London including restaurants, pubs, gigs, and sightseeing tips, especially if you have an interest in doing things that are a bit out of the ordinary. 

I work part time in Corporate Governance at a housing association in East London. I often work from home - essentially I can work from anywhere as long as I have a WiFi connection. 

I've done a lot of travelling including the USA, Europe and South East Asia. My travels in the last year have included Thailand, New York City, Barcelona, the Scottish Highlands and Wales. Next up (hopefully) is Lisbon, the Isles of Scilly, and then Italy. Too many places, too little time! The photo in my profile is of me and my boyfriend in Killarney National Park, Ireland two years ago. Loved it.

neighborhood_overview:
Clapham is a varied, vibrant area of South London comprising of a huge Common, and a long High Street. Due to the area's size, as you'd expect, there's a great deal of variation in pretty much everything. It has an appealing mix of good transport links, urban character and plenty of attractive period homes which make it one of the most flourishing and sought after parts of south London. Shopping, transport connections and the social scene make it a truly fantastic place to stay. Clapham residents from all walks of life are united by the eponymous Common. Despite being surrounded by busy arterial roads, it is a broad and tranquil green space beloved by all locals. A focal point for the community, all manner of sporting events and activities take place, as well as annual events including the popular SW4 festival.

neighborhood_overview:
Even if you don't end up actually staying here, Shoreditch is a must-see part of London for any visitor. Its mix of filmset-perfect cobbled streets of early Georgian townhouses sit alongside converted warehouses and graffiti murals aplenty.

Many of the artist residents who first made the area hip have had to move away on account of rising house prices, but there's still plenty to see and the area is ram-packed full of small galleries, independent boutiques and some of London's coolest bars and restaurants.

The spacious bedroom features neutral tones and chic furnishings that add character to the space. You'll hav
neighborhood_overview:
Canary Wharf is both a leading financial centre and a tourist destination in its own right.

The complex is home to ten skyscrapers with a height of more than 160 metres and contains about 1.5 million square metres of office space. It is built around the now disused West India Docks, one of the world's busiest docks from the start of the 19th century until the outbreak of World War Two.

These days, Canary Wharf is one of the United Kingdom’s two international financial centres, alongside the City of London.

Canary Wharf also offers urban living at its best: stunning modern architecture, impressive public spaces, great transport links, and world class shopping, restaurants, bars, gyms and other amenities.

Canary Wharf is home to the impressive Museum of London: Docklands and Billingsgate Market. The excellent Mudchute City Farm, the O2 Arena and the attractions of Greenwich are found nearby.

neighborhood_overview:
Perfectly placed near London’s Victoria Station.

Situated on a peaceful residential street in Pimlico, one of London’s prettiest and most central areas, The Melita is perfectly located to enjoy the best that London, one of the world’s most exhilarating cities, has to offer. Only a hop, skip and a jump from Buckingham Palace, Big Ben and the Houses of Parliament, the hotel is perfectly placed for work or pleasure.

Local coffee shops are just a 2 minute walk away, as well as local restaurants covering a wide variety of cuisines and supermarkets within 5-10 minutes of the hotel.
host_about:
We are an independent family run bed and breakfast, which has been offering private rooms with friendly service for nearly half a Century, but we're new to the wonderful world of Airbnb. :-)

We are known for our independent style and beautiful white stucco buildings which are nearly 200 years old.

Our ethos is  to offer homely rooms in a historic setting, just a stones throw from the major tourist attractions and with friendly help on hand 15 hours/day. This is what sets us apart. 

We love finding and recommending affordable new independent restaurants, spending time with our families, and we have a strong passion for art. So much so, that we run a non-profit artistic initiative to support up and coming artists. We have transformed our property into a non-profit art gallery hosting original pieces of art by 170 artists from over 35 countries. Check it out on Instagram at #MelitaSupportingTheArts. Airbnb is about unique properties, and we are unique. 

We also love meeting new people, hearing our guest's stories and sharing their and our top tips for fun things to do in town with new guests.

neighborhood_overview:
King’s Cross might be best known for its bustling train stations linking London to other parts of the country, as well as the continent, but a recent host of developments have regenerated the area, with new restaurants, bars and pubs popping up.

There are plenty of other things to do as well, with outstanding clubs, music venues and museums nearby, much-loved green spaces and a pretty stretch of Regent’s Canal, all of which makes King’s Cross an ace destination in its own right. If you’re feeling cultured, pop to the famous British Library which boasts an impressive events calendar packed with exhibitions and talks all year long. Shop at the brand new Coal Drops Yard and, if you end up feeling peckish, wander over to Kerb food market or the restaurants that line Granary Square. We absolutely understand if you need to make a detour to King’s Cross station for your snap at Harry Potter’s Platform 9¾
